The paper deals with mechanism design for auctions, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of social networks in auctions suggests a possible connection to social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves optimization and revenue analysis, which could fall under control theory (cs.CY) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the analysis of incentives and efficiency could also relate to machine learning (cs.LG).
